---
import SectionTitle from './SectionTitle.astro';
const facts = [
  ['Years building', '8+'],
  ['Production deploys', '3,400+'],
  ['Languages spoken', 'ES · EN · PT'],
  ['Coffee preference', 'Filter, Huila'],
  ['Tabs or spaces', 'Two spaces'],
  ['Editor', 'Neovim → VS Code'],
];
---
<section id="about" class="about">
  <div class="container">
    <SectionTitle
      index="02"
      kicker="About"
      title="An engineer with a craftsman's temperament."
    />
    <div class="about-grid">
      <div>
        <div class="portrait">
          <div class="portrait-tag">[ portrait — drop image ]</div>
        </div>
        <div class="reading-card">
          <div class="reading-label">Currently reading</div>
          <p class="reading-title">"The Pragmatic Programmer", 20th Anniversary Ed.</p>
          <p class="reading-author">— Hunt &amp; Thomas</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="serif pull-quote-mark">"</div>
        <p class="pull-quote">
          The systems I care about are the ones that survive the boring Tuesday at 4pm
          when someone needs to debug them.
        </p>
        <div class="about-facts">
          {facts.map(([k, v]) => (
            <div class="about-fact">
              <div class="about-fact-k">{k}</div>
              <div class="about-fact-v">{v}</div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
        <div class="about-body">
          <p>
            I spent the first half of my career building consumer products and the second
            half building the infrastructure underneath them. The pattern I keep returning
            to: pay attention to the seams, name things precisely, and don't be clever
            where you can be clear.
          </p>
          <p>
            Outside of work I write short essays on systems thinking, run a weekly local
            meetup for backend engineers in Bogotá, and am slowly learning to bind books
            by hand.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
